trailingComments.value: Represents ownership (necessary when the item is moved which triggers callbacks)

leadingComments.value: Represents ownership (necessary when the item is moved which triggers callbacks)
Disable drag&drop if handle wasn't found
Do it in the next frame so that the removing animation is visible

trailingComments.value: In case an already connected element is switched to new parent,
we need to ignore the connected callback in that case as well which is correct,
as the item will be connected to new parent and messenger needs to be informed as well parent.
Hence posting connected in update callback.
